1. DATASETS IN USE
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

### C3GD — Certus Caliber Classification Gunshot Dataset
    Used for:  gunshot detection + weapon/caliber classification baseline
               (docs/SENTINEL-SHOTS-FIRED.md P1/P2/P4)
    Authors:   Sinclair Gurny, Ryan Quinn (Stonewall Defense LLC dba Certus
               Innovations)
    Source:    https://zenodo.org/records/20274400
    Paper:     "Descriptor: Certus Caliber Classification Gunshot Dataset (C3GD)"
               arXiv:2606.18135
    License:   Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
               https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/
    Commercial use: PERMITTED with attribution.
    Contents:  8,000+ field-collected shots, 28 firearms, 16 calibers.

    ATTRIBUTION: "Certus Caliber Classification Gunshot Dataset (C3GD)" by
    Sinclair Gurny and Ryan Quinn, licensed under CC BY 4.0.

    NOTE: the C3GD descriptor paper and the Certus training-code README cite
    DIFFERENT Zenodo record ids (20274400 vs 20737299) — likely a versioned
    re-release. Resolve and pin the exact record id + version here before
    training, so results are reproducible against a known snapshot.


### FSD50K — Freesound Dataset 50k
    Used for:  CONFOUNDER corpus (fireworks, door slams, hammering,
               construction, thunder, engine backfire) — the false-positive
               fight described in docs/SENTINEL-SHOTS-FIRED.md §10.
    Authors:   Eduardo Fonseca, Xavier Favory, Jordi Pons, Frederic Font,
               Xavier Serra (Music Technology Group, Universitat Pompeu Fabra)
    Source:    https://zenodo.org/records/4060432
    Paper:     "FSD50K: An Open Dataset of Human-Labeled Sound Events"
               arXiv:2010.00475
    License:   The dataset AS A WHOLE is CC BY 4.0. Individual clips carry
               their OWN licenses, assigned by the original Freesound uploader:
                 CC0            19,873 clips  (38.8%)  — no attribution needed
                 CC-BY          23,506 clips  (45.9%)  — attribution required
                 CC-BY-NC        6,041 clips  (11.8%)  — NOT USED (see §2)
                 CC Sampling+    1,777 clips   (3.5%)  — NOT USED (see §2)

    *** ONLY THE CC0 AND CC-BY CLIPS ARE USED. ***

    Enforcement is mechanical, not manual: tools/fsd50k_license_filter.mjs
    reads the upstream dev_clips_info_FSD50K.json / eval_clips_info_FSD50K.json
    license maps, emits a training whitelist containing ONLY CC0 + CC-BY clips,
    and generates the per-clip attribution list at NOTICE-fsd50k-clips.txt.
    Run it before training; commit its output.

    ATTRIBUTION: "FSD50K" by Eduardo Fonseca, Xavier Favory, Jordi Pons,
    Frederic Font and Xavier Serra, licensed under CC BY 4.0. Per-clip
    attributions for the CC-BY clips actually used: see
    NOTICE-fsd50k-clips.txt.


